cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT

The paper proposes a framework that utilizes deep neural networks to predict unmeasured network attributes using end-to-end path measurements. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with network monitoring and inference, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the reconstruction of network topology, which could make it relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
